## Test Organization

### File Structure
- Place tests in `src/__tests__/` or `src/tests/` directory
- Match component/test file names: `UserCard.test.jsx`, `api-handler.spec.ts`
- Group related tests in folders when appropriate

### Testing Frameworks
- Use Jest for JavaScript/TypeScript projects  
- Use React Testing Library for component testing
- Implement proper test coverage thresholds (minimum 80%)
- Include integration tests for critical paths

## Test Writing Guidelines

### Test Structure
```javascript
describe('UserCard Component', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    // Setup before each test
  });

  afterEach(() => {
    // Cleanup after each test
  });

  test('renders user name correctly', () => {
    const { getByText } = render(<UserCard user={{ name: 'John Doe' }} />);
    expect(getByText('John Doe')).toBeInTheDocument();
  });

  test('handles click event', () => {
    const handleClick = jest.fn();
    const { getByRole } = render(
      <UserCard user={{ name: 'John Doe' }} onClick={handleClick} />
    );
    
    fireEvent.click(getByRole('button'));
    expect(handleClick).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
  });
});
```

## Code Quality Standards

### Test Coverage
- Aim for 80%+ test coverage
- Focus on business logic and critical paths
- Include edge cases and error conditions  
- Mock external dependencies appropriately

### Configuration Validation Testing
- All configuration values should be tested for validity
- Edge cases in numeric configurations should be covered 
- Environment-specific configurations should be validated
- Test failure scenarios for invalid configuration settings

### Performance Tests
- Test component rendering performance
- Measure API response times
- Implement proper loading states in tests

## Continuous Integration

### CI/CD Requirements
- Run tests automatically on commit
- Fail builds on test failures or coverage drops
- Include linting and formatting checks
- Generate coverage reports

### Configuration Testing
- Configuration validation should be tested as part of CI pipeline  
- Environment-specific configurations should be validated in staging
- Test configuration changes against production-like scenarios
